<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/459:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-22T18:00:00+08:00">November 22, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 22—11:15
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1026. My 1020, November 21, noon. Following from American Consul at
                            Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“November 21, 6 p.m. It has been learned from official source
                                    today that Manchuli and Chalainor have both been captured by the
                                    Soviets. General Han and another general, name unknown, were
                                    captured; latter committed suicide.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>